                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" scribe="MarEyj001" script="unknown">Ff. 3r-78v and 92r-144v (except for the account covering the years
                        1737) are written by the samme hand. According to <name type="person"
                           key="RasRas001">Rask</name> this hand belongs to <name type="person"
                           key="MarEyj001">Markús Eyjólfsson</name>.</handNote>
                     <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown">Ff. 79r-92r are written by another hand.</handNote>
                     <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown" scribe="JonHel002">Ff. 151r-160v written by the <foreign xml:lang="is"
                           >sýslumaður</foreign>
                        <name type="person" key="JonHel002">Jón Helgason</name>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions><name type="person" key="RasRas001">Rask</name> wrote that item 1 was
                     in <q>hönd Sra <name type="person" key="MarEyj001">Marcúsar Eyjólfssonar</name>
                        á Söndum f. V.</q>; on p. 1 he added a similar, yet unreliable, account on
                     the scribe of item 2. Item 4 is said to be a copy of <name type="person"
                        key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name>'s copy of the diploma; item 5 is
                     supposedly <q>aflavsum rotnum bl&#xE7D3;dum epter Syslum. <name type="person"
                           key="OrmDad001">Orm Dada Son</name>.</q>
                  </additions>
